  <p>Proper nutrition is one of the most important factors in your pet's long-term health. All About Pets Veterinary Hospital provides nutritional counseling to help you make informed dietary choices for your cat or dog.</p>

  <h2>Why Nutrition Matters</h2>
  <p>Every pet has different nutritional needs based on their age, breed, weight, activity level, and any existing health conditions. The right diet can help prevent obesity, support organ function, strengthen the immune system, and improve your pet's energy and quality of life.</p>

  <h3>Our Nutritional Counseling Includes</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Assessment of your pet's current diet and body condition</li>
    <li>Customized feeding recommendations</li>
    <li>Weight management plans for overweight pets</li>
    <li>Dietary guidance for pets with medical conditions (diabetes, kidney disease, allergies)</li>
    <li>Advice on supplements and treats</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Good nutrition can make a real difference in how your pet feels every day. Contact us to discuss your pet's dietary needs.</p>
